    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26.42-43_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">42</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Feb. 14, 1958</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear John,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>More good news. Remember the idea I told you about before I left of filming a trip down the Missouri River? Well, I think I have found a bu<del>c<unclear/>er</del><add>yer</add> for the film. If all goes well, <del>I</del><add>i</add>t will be shown on network <hi rend="caps">TV</hi> from coast to coast.</p>
 
                <p>Here is what the plan is so far. Two or three of us would sail down the river photographing the adventure as we go. I would like very much to have you in some of the pictures. When the film is completed then you will narrate it with parts from "The Song of Three Friends" and possibly from parts of "The River and I." Do you like the idea? I think it is a real fine adventure film idea and the man I talked to said it was almost a cinch that it would be bought.</p>
                
                <p>I know this is asking a lot, but can you any a fairly short length of time put together a very rough draft of a script? You, of course, know the river and what parts of it would make good story material. I think that a combination of straight narration and excerpts from <hi rend="underline"><del>"</del>The Cycle of the West</hi> would be the best idea. You might e<del>b</del><add>v</add>en toy with the idea of doing it in <del>v</del><add>r</add>e<del>r</del><add>v</add>erse order, that is to start at St. Louis and work up the river (of course it would be filmed by floating down the river) or it might be done with the idea of the trappers coming back down stream with furs. I don't know enough about the material yet to say which would be best.</p>
                
                <p>So if you like the idea, can you drop me a line and let me know, and then start on a very rough script so that I can have something to show the people who will be buying the film?</p>
                
                <p>I will <del>right</del><add>write</add> more latter<sic>later</sic>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Your friend,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Sandy</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
